==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isocephalism
<hw>I`so*ceph"a*lism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Gr. <?/
like-headed. See <er>Iso-</er>, and <er>Cephalon</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Art)</fld> <def>A peculiarity in the design of bas-relief by which
the heads of human figures are kept at the same height from the ground,
whether the personages are seated, standing, or mounted on horseback; --
called also <altname>isokephaleia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isochasm</ent>⟦br⟧
